⬇️⬇️ Links, schedule, and more information down below! ⬇️⬇️

Welcome! Come join for some motivation and accountability! Here we follow the 50/10 Pomodoro method, where we work for 50 minutes and then take a 10 minute break to chat, relax, craft and play puzzles! (we're obsessed with jumble words...)

I am a physics PhD student in my second year at the University of Auckland. My PhD is purely theoretical and computational, so I do lots of coding. My research looks at gravitational wave physics in relation to supermassive black holes and the future Laser Interferometer Space Antenna.

I did my undergraduate and masters in the UK, where I grew up, and then moved to New Zealand for my PhD. I now do purely research and don't take any classes, but I do teach some!

- have drinks/food ready so you don't have to get up to go get necessities
- have a clear idea of what you want to accomplish during the session (i.e., choose a task from your to-do list)


✧･ﾟ during the breaks:
- stop working as soon as the timer hits, even if you're mid-sentence
- make sure to get up, do some simple stretches
- refill anything that needs to get refilled
- talk to friends/update family

✧･ﾟ at the end of this video:
if you want to continue studying, give yourself a longer break and you can the next session video!

you're set to go! ♡

To those who are starting :
In order to study or do anything for long periods of time you need a strong purpose and you must be willing to endure challenges. If I can do this, think about what you can accomplish. If you're starting out, start from low intervals(10-30 minutes) and gradually increase once you feel you're comfortable. If you feel like quitting, visualize your goals and evaluate your purpose. Learn to accept challenges in your life to become uncommon.

Boost Your Productivity with My "Study With Me" Pomodoro 50/10 Live Session on YouTube

Looking for the perfect way to stay motivated and productive while studying or working? Join my "Study With Me" live session, where we use the powerful Pomodoro Technique to break down tasks into focused intervals. This method combines 50 minutes of deep focus with 10-minute refreshing breaks, helping you stay on track and avoid burnout.

Why Join This Live Session?

Stay Accountable: Working alongside others in real-time keeps you motivated and minimizes procrastination.

Structured Focus Time: The 50/10 Pomodoro cycle promotes sustained concentration, making it ideal for studying, writing, reading, or any productive activity.

Relaxing Study Vibes: Enjoy a calm and distraction-free environment with background music or ambient sounds to help you concentrate.

Community Support: Connect with like-minded individuals in the live chat who are also striving to achieve their goals.

Perfect for Everyone: Whether you’re a student preparing for exams, a professional working on a project, or simply someone with a passion for learning, this session is for you!


What to Expect:

1. A timer-guided Pomodoro session with clear transitions between focus and break times.


2. Tips and encouragement to help you maintain your focus.


3. A warm and welcoming space where you can share your goals, progress, and challenges in the live chat.



How the Pomodoro Technique Works:
The Pomodoro method is simple yet highly effective. You work on a task for a set amount of time (50 minutes in this case) and then take a short break (10 minutes). This structured approach:

Reduces mental fatigue.

Improves time management skills.

Encourages consistent progress without feeling overwhelmed.


Why Choose the 50/10 Variation?
While the traditional Pomodoro technique uses 25/5 intervals, the 50/10 variation is better suited for deeper work and more complex tasks. It allows you to fully immerse yourself in your work while giving your brain ample time to rest during breaks.

What You’ll Achieve:
